    {
      "text": "Puyo Puyo~n (ぷよぷよ〜ん, Puyopuyōn), also known as Puyo Puyo 4 and Puyo Puyo~n Party (for the N64 version), is a 1999 puzzle video game and the fourth installment of the Puyo Puyo series, created by Compile for the Dreamcast, PlayStation, Nintendo 64 and Game Boy Color. Like many of the Puyo Puyo games, it was never officially released outside Japan. The title of Puyo Puyo~n comes from the Japanese word yon (四; meaning four), signifying the fourth game in the series.",
